  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Avanti iKnowledge - Phase 2 work - Call 1</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall aim of iKnowledge is to transform the
learning environment in schools for children and
teachers in Tanzania through improved sustainable
infrastructure, teacher development and enhanced
use of quality educational content.
Teachers in Tanzanian schools do not have
adequate internet access or online resources for
teaching. The project delivers internet access to more
than 250 schools across Tanzania and has also
set up example schools in other African countries.
Selected Academy and Teaching Lab schools are
also provided with online educational resources.
As part of the sustainability plan, a few selected
iKnowledge schools are installed with a Wi-Fi
Community Access Point to generate revenue
to subsidise internet access.
The expected outcome of the project is to provide
a sustainable level of ICT literacy for school teachers
and sufficient revenue generated through the network.</narrative>
  </description>
